A simple python solution using [Trie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trie)
Does this problem need a trie? No! But I solved it using a Tire anyway. 

```
class Solution:
    def prefixCount(self, words: List[str], pref: str) -> int:
        trie = {}

        for word in words:
            self.insert(trie, word)
        return self.getPrefixCount(trie, pref)

    def insert(self, trie, word):
        for ch in word:
            if ch not in trie:
                trie[ch] = [1, {}]
            else:
                trie[ch][0] += 1

            trie = trie[ch][1]


    def getPrefixCount(self, trie, pref):
        lastNode = None
        for ch in pref:
            if ch not in trie:
                return 0

            lastNode = trie[ch][0]
            trie = trie[ch][1]

        return lastNode
```

