# Intuition
Since it was a minimise the maximum kind of problem a very classic problem usually solved by binary search 
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
So we should use $$binary\ search$$ as well 
Here we will assume an aswer and try to verify that our assumed answer is possible or not. Our answer may lie between 1 sec to the time taken if all the trip was made by the maximum time taking bus. 
Finding maximum will be adding another O(N) to our solution, avoiding that in our case, so according to the constraints the maximum possible answer will be LONG_MAX so we set our high limit as the same. Then we will use binary search to search our answer in the range if answer exists then we will find another better answer that is minimum then the previous.
For determining whether the probable answer is possible or not we can iterate over the array and count how many trips would be completed by each bus in the probable time(mid).
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n*log(LLONG\_MAX))$$ where in n is the size of the array time
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$ as no extra space used 
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPossible(vector<int>& time, int totalTrips, long long mid){
        long long count = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < time.size(); i++){
            count += mid / time[i];
            if(count >= totalTrips) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
    long long minimumTime(vector<int>& time, int totalTrips) {
        long long low = 1;
        long long high = LLONG_MAX;
        long long ans;
        while(low <= high){
            long long mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            if(isPossible(time, totalTrips, mid)){
                ans = mid;
                high = mid - 1;
            } else{
                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
