# Approach
To solve this problem, we can use binary search. We can assume a range of possible values for the minimum time required for all buses to complete at least totalTrips trips. We can start with the range [0, max(time) * totalTrips], where max(time) is the maximum time taken by any bus for one trip.

We can then perform binary search on this range to find the minimum time required. For each mid value in the range, we can calculate the total number of trips that can be completed in that time by all the buses. If the total number of trips is less than totalTrips, then we can search for a higher value of mid. Otherwise, we can search for a lower value of mid.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n log m)



# Code
