# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Whenever we get any problem , we should find all the useful hints/ details from the problem . 
Here looking at constraints we can find than **O(n log n)** is the **worst allowed time complexity** .

We can use **binary_search** to get O(n log n) solution . We need to get more strong details to used binary_search , can we bound 'time_taken' ?
Yes **minimun time** possible = 1, and **max_time_taken** = (max_value* tot_trips)  in worst case **max_vaue = 10^7** and **tot_trips = 10^7** ,
so **max_time_taken = 10^14** for all the test cases .


Now we can confirm that **Binary search** can be implemented.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We implemetn binary serach in range [1,10^14] ,
and for each **mid** value we will find the tot_trips_possible ,
if (tot_trips_possible >= tot_trips),
then we reduce the range from [start,end] -- > [start,mid-1]
else if not possible then we change from [start,end] -- > [mid+1,end]
computer the **mid = (start+end)/2**  again and continue.
Until our binary seearch continue and update the answer too.


